Tazobactam S Tobramycin S n a n a n a n a n a n a n a n a n a Chest xray T 0 Interval placement of double lumen endotracheal tube one lumen terminating at the level of the aortic knob and the other selectively within the left mainstem bronchus Otherwise no significant change with patchy opacities in the right lung and pleural thickening at the right apex see impression Chest ct T 4 1 Significant consolidation scattered tree in bud opacities scattered ground glass opacities throughout the lungs worse in the lower lobes consistent with pneumonia Multiple air cysts are present within the right upper lung and some contain debris suspicious for fungal infection such as a mycetoma Many of these lung cysts in the right upper lobe demonstrate air fluid levels as well and are likely infected Given the degree of consolidation and nodular opacities underlying malignancy is not ruled out in these regions Overall this is significantly worsened pneumonia n a n a n a n a after punct removed
